==English==
===Etymology===
From the Aboriginal language [[Dharuk]], [[bumariny]].

===Noun===
'''boomerang''' (plural: [[boomerangs]])

#Flat curved [[airfoil]] originally thrown by Australian Aborigines to kill animals, nowadays mostly used for sports. Boomerangs can be of the returnable or non-returnable kind. The returnable ones can not be used to kill animals, but for sports or training.

